      "content": "I can provide you with a framework that focuses on identifying leadership qualities and communication styles that are often valued in corporate environments, regardless of educational background. Here are some qualitative criteria to consider:\n\n1. Leadership Readiness:\n   - Initiative: Look for evidence of self-starting behavior and the ability to take charge of projects.\n   - Decision-making: Assess their track record in making tough decisions and the outcomes of those decisions.\n   - Influence: Consider how they have persuaded or led others to follow their vision or direction.\n   - Adaptability: Evaluate their ability to adjust to new challenges and environments.\n   - Vision: Determine if they have a clear idea of where they want to take the team or project and how they plan to get there.\n\n2. Communication Style:\n   - Clarity: Assess their ability to convey complex ideas in a clear and understandable manner.\n   - Consistency: Look for a consistent communication style that aligns with the company's values and culture.\n   - Empathy: Consider their ability to understand and relate to others' perspectives and feelings.\n   - Feedback: Evaluate their willingness to give and receive constructive feedback.\n   - Collaboration: Look for evidence of teamwork and the ability to work well with others.\n\nRemember, these criteria are meant to",
      "source": "target",
